{"questionId":"15807","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The function <em>f</em> : <em><strong>M</strong></em> → <em><strong>M</strong></em> where <em><strong>M</strong></em> is the set of 2 × 2 matrices, is given by <em>f</em>(<em><strong>X</strong></em>) = <em><strong>AX</strong></em> where <em><strong>A</strong></em> is a 2 × 2 matrix.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Given that <em><strong>A</strong></em> is non-singular, prove that<em> f</em> is a bijection.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This question is from an exam for a previous syllabus, and may contain minor differences in marking or structure.</p><p>suppose <em>f</em>(<em><strong>X</strong></em>) = <em>f</em>(<em><strong>Y</strong></em>) , ie <em><strong>AX</strong></em> = <em><strong>AY</strong></em>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>then <em><strong>A</strong></em><sup>−1</sup><strong><em>AX</em></strong> = <em><strong>A</strong></em><sup>−1</sup><strong><em>AY&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><em><strong>X</strong></em> = <em><strong>Y&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>since <em>f</em>(<em><strong>X</strong></em>) =&nbsp;<em>f</em>(<em><strong>Y</strong></em>) ⇒&nbsp;<em><strong>X</strong></em>&nbsp;=&nbsp;<em><strong>Y</strong></em>, <em>f</em> is an injection&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>now suppose <strong>C</strong> ∈ <em><strong>M</strong></em> and consider <em>f</em>(<em><strong>D</strong></em>) = <em><strong>C</strong></em> , ie <em><strong>AD</strong></em> = <em><strong>C&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>then <em><strong>D</strong></em> = <em><strong>A</strong></em><sup>−1</sup>&nbsp;<em><strong>C</strong></em>&nbsp;(<em><strong>A</strong></em><sup>−1</sup> exists since <em><strong>A</strong></em> is non- singular)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>since given <strong>C</strong>&nbsp;∈&nbsp;<em><strong>M</strong></em>, there exists <em><strong>D</strong></em>&nbsp;∈&nbsp;<em><strong>M</strong></em> such that <em>f</em>(<em><strong>D</strong></em>) = <em><strong>C</strong></em> , <em>f</em> is&nbsp;a surjection&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>therefore<em> f</em> is a bijection&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[7</strong></em><strong style=\"font-style:italic;\">&nbsp;marks]</strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"15807","referenceCode":"19M.1.AHL.TZ0.F_13a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Given that A is non-singular, prove that f is a bijection.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 7]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Introduction to matrices"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}